        - <name>x_casemgmt_validate_open_transition</name> - subflow
          name preserved character-for-character per the AAP
          file-naming convention.
        - <internal_name> matches <name>.
        - <sys_update_name>sys_hub_flow_x_casemgmt_validate_open_transition</sys_update_name>
          - the Update Set tracking key follows the pattern
          <table>_<record_name>.
        - <sys_scope>x_casemgmt</sys_scope> binds THIS subflow record
          to the scoped application's scope record by NAME (no
          hardcoded sys_id literal).
        - <sys_package> binds THIS subflow record to the scoped
          application's sys_app record by NAME (no hardcoded sys_id
          literal). The display_value="Case Management" attribute and
          source="x_casemgmt" attribute are platform conventions for
          the Update Set engine to resolve the package binding at
          import time.
        - All references inside <latest_snapshot> / <master_snapshot>
          use stable name lookups: "reference_table": "x_casemgmt_case"
          (BY NAME), "x_casemgmt.CaseTransitionValidator" (BY API
          NAME). Zero hardcoded sys_id literals appear in the
          snapshot JSON.

