          validate_inprogress_transition with sys_id
          f8117474ee1542c4e6aacd477fdef910 and
          validate_resolved_transition with sys_id
          c8fde9d4675c53e1c14e40c0503835f0 and
          validate_pending_transition with sys_id
          94063d7d535c4e841ad7deb0b45e8ba5).

    ACTIVE / PUBLISHED STATE (assigned-folder rule per AAP gate 7):

        - <active>true</active> - subflow is enabled, NOT Draft. Per
          the assigned-folder requirements: "Each subflow MUST be set
          to Active = true (not Draft) before Update Set export." A
          Draft subflow would be skipped by the parent flow's
          dispatch and the precondition gate would not fire,
          silently allowing invalid Draft -> Open transitions.
        - <status>published</status> - subflow is published, NOT
          draft. Together with active=true, this guarantees the
          subflow is invocable by parent flows immediately after
          Update Set commit.
        - <validation_status>complete</validation_status> - Flow
          Designer's pre-publish validation has been run and the
          subflow has zero validation errors.

    NO-EMAIL CONSTRAINT (AAP Section 0.7.2 + assigned-folder rule 7):

        - The subflow contains ZERO "Send Email" actions, ZERO
          gs.eventQueue() calls, ZERO sn_notification API
