    VALIDATION GATE MAPPING (AAP Section 0.7.3):

        - Gate 2 (Workflow): "All state transitions enforced for both
          case types - Invalid transitions return blocking error;
          task-closure check blocks Resolved transition." THIS subflow
          contributes to Gate 2 by ENFORCING the assigned_group
          precondition for the Draft -> Open transition on BOTH case
          types (General Inquiry and Complaint). The gate is verified
          by:

              1) Create a case in 'Draft' status with assigned_group
                 EMPTY.
              2) Attempt to set the case's status to 'Open' (e.g., via
                 the form's Save button).
              3) The parent flow (general_inquiry or complaint
                 state_machine, depending on case.type) fires on
                 the OnUpdate trigger filtered to status -> Open.
              4) The parent flow calls this subflow with
                 case_record = $trigger.current.
              5) This subflow's Script Step runs the validator,
                 which detects assigned_group is empty.
              6) The validator returns
                 { ok: false, error: 'Required field assigned_group is empty.' }
              7) This subflow's If condition (ok == false) is true.
              8) The Throw Error action fires with the message.
              9) The parent flow's transaction aborts; the form
                 displays the error.
             10) The case row remains at status='Draft' (the update
                 was rolled back; the new value 'Open' was never
                 persisted).

          Then with assigned_group set to a valid group:
              1) Update the case to set assigned_group = (some group).
              2) Attempt to set the case's status to 'Open'.
              3) The parent flow fires; this subflow's Script Step
                 runs the validator, which detects assigned_group is
                 populated.
              4) The validator returns { ok: true }.
              5) This subflow's If condition is false; Throw Error
                 does NOT fire.
              6) The parent flow proceeds; the status update is
                 persisted; the case is now Open.

        - Gate 7 (Update Set): "Scoped app exported - Update Set
          loads without errors on a fresh PDI instance." The
          deterministic sys_id, reference-by-name pattern, and well-
          formed XML structure ensure this record re-imports cleanly
          with zero preview errors. The CDATA-wrapped JSON snapshot
          contains characters requiring CDATA escaping (curly braces,
          quotes within JSON, the != comparison operator), and the
          CDATA section is properly opened and closed around both
          <latest_snapshot> and <master_snapshot> elements.

    PERFORMANCE NOTE:

        canTransitionToOpen does a single GlideRecord field read
        (caseGr.getValue('assigned_group')), no GlideRecord query, no
        GlideAggregate, and no external system calls. The gate path
        is essentially zero-cost - the validator returns in under a
        millisecond regardless of the case row size or the number of
        related records. There is no N+1 query risk; there is no
        join; there is no aggregation. The subflow scaffolding adds
        only the Flow Designer dispatch overhead (a single
        synchronous step + an If branch). For the common case where
        assigned_group IS populated (the vast majority of legitimate
        Draft -> Open transitions), the gate path is exactly:

            field-read -> ok=true -> if-false -> return.

        For the failure case (assigned_group not populated):

            field-read -> ok=false -> if-true -> throw_error -> abort.

        Both paths complete well under 10 milliseconds.

    FUTURE EXTENSIBILITY:

        - If a future AAP enhancement adds a 'Reopened' status that
          allows transitions from Closed back to Open, this subflow
          would still apply (the validator is status-source-agnostic)
          and would still enforce the assigned_group gate. The gate
          is on the DESTINATION status (Open), not the source, so
          it transparently handles re-entry.
        - If the assigned_group precondition is later replaced by a
          more complex rule (e.g., assigned_group must be one of a
          whitelisted set of "intake" groups), only the Script
          Include's canTransitionToOpen helper needs to change; this
          subflow continues to work unchanged because it consumes the
          unified { ok, error } shape returned by the validator.
        - If email is later re-enabled on the PDI and a "Case is now
          Open - awaiting agent assignment" notification is desired,
          add a Send Email step to the parent flows (after this
          subflow returns successfully), NOT to this subflow. This
          subflow's responsibility is gating only; notification is
          a separate concern.
        - If a Pending -> Open back-edge is added (currently not in
          AAP Section 0.5.5), this subflow can be reused as-is on
          that edge because the precondition (assigned_group
          populated) holds equally on entry from any source state.
